content.text:
Eyewash Stations

Instructions
  1. Ensure the eyewash station is readily accessible. Move all obstructions away from the station.
  2. Most stations will be installed above a sink/drain. If there is no sink/drain, obtain a bucket/pan to capture the water from the test, or funnel it into the sink.
  3. Activate the station for a minimum of 3-minutes.
  4. The protective cap(s) should come off automatically and the water temperature should stabilize. A 3-minute flush allows for the removal of any build-up in the system.
  5. After 3-minutes, deactivate the unit, clean-up any spilled water, and initial the test below.

If there are any deficiencies found in the weekly test, contact the maintenance desk at 780-492-4833.

name.text: Have eyewash stations been flushed in the last week?

description.text: If you answer Yes to the above question, please provide the room number, date of the last annual test, and the year built for each eyewash station you flushed.

name.text: Have all sinks been flushed for 3 minutes?
Is all appropriate PPE being worn?
